## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the exact pattern recommended in the official Vercel documentation:

```jsx
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* app content */}
      <Analytics />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Next Steps for Deployment

To fully enable Web Analytics on Vercel:

1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard:
   - Navigate to your project settings
   - Go to the Analytics tab
   - Click the "Enable" button
3. Analytics data will start appearing after users visit the deployed site

## Framework Details
- **Framework**: React 19.1.0 with Vite 6.3.5
- **Package Manager**: npm (package-lock.json present)
- **Build System**: Vite
- **Configuration**: Standard React/Vite setup

## Notes
- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact application performance
- Analytics data collection complies with privacy regulations
- The current setup supports both standard page view analytics and Speed Insights
- No environment variables or additional configuration files are required for basic functionality
